DDJ. chapter.57

The 1st sentence:
"yi zheng zhi guo,
yi qi yong bing,
yi WU SHI qu tian xia"

The last sentence:
So the sage said:
"wo WU WEI, er min zi hua;
wo hao jing, er min zi zheng;
wo WU SHI, er min zi fu;
wo wu yu, er min zi pu."

There are 2 words--wu wei and wushi in these 2 sentences.
I'd like to express what's my understanding of these 2 words.

Wuwei: a highest state of one's spirituality/ world view. already have
discerned the true appearance of the world and all creature, shuffle off
this mortal coil, get rid of the cord of illusioned "self".(the self
cause=&gt;you and I ,my and your, different races ,different countries ...etc
all kind of differential heart. It is the source of our inexhaustible
suffering/tragedy/worry/resentment/unwisdom...), understanding the world is
an unity and how it works. Understanding that to regard others/creature is
love yourself......etc.
very close to the concept of "Nirvana"

Wushi: having no deliberate (intentional) purpose and
implies non-interference in the natural order. Frequently
it is misinterpreted to mean doing nothing which can be
wrongly mapped to the Western idiom of a "carelessness"
or an indifferent "laissez-faire" attitude.
(it is copied from Shazi'post before, but shazi give this definition to
"Wuwei")

Why so many people misunderstand wuwei so many years?
my point of view is they mix up with the Rujia'wuwei.
The word "wuwei" also used by Rujia/confucian/Confucianism.
The influence of rujia/confucian/Confucianism is far-reaching in Chinese
culture/politics.
"Once a use forever a custom."

So,
"wo WU WEI, er min zi hua; wo WU SHI, er min zi fu"  can be apprehended as:

"if I(governer) attain to as high as wuwei level of world view or I'm
working hard try to heighten my consciousness to wuwei,(i'm an example)
then people will spontaneous follow me to civilize their spirituality
(no need promote by words).
if I(governer) having no deliberate (intentional) purpose and
implies to intervene in the affairs of state,
then people will involuntary get rich."

tttt.
