Yes.
Wu Wei seems to connote spontaneity
in the sense of no premeditated action.
It may also literally denote non-action.
It suggests or connotes effortless action
or action without action, wei-wu-wei.

Wu Shi might mean the same thing.

And\or:
Wu Shi seems to connote not meddling with
or not bothering or not troubling people.

It might be much less
than not having a deliberate
nor intentional purpose.

It's one non-action to allow mud to settle.
It's another not-meddle to not stir things up.

